        <name>SelectNext</name>
        <qualifiedname>Assets.Scripts.Scheduling.Core.DispatchingRules.SelectNext</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>List&lt; <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1_1_operation" kindref="compound">Operation</ref> &gt;</type>
          <declname>waitingOps</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1_1_job" kindref="compound">Job</ref>[]</type>
          <declname>allJobs</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87" kindref="member">DispatchingRule</ref></type>
          <declname>rule</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Selects the next operation to process from a machine&apos;s waiting queue. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Applies the given <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87" kindref="member">DispatchingRule</ref> to rank all waiting operations, with ties broken by lowest job ID to match job_shop_lib&apos;s default ordering. Returns immediately if the queue contains zero or one entries, avoiding unnecessary sorting overhead. Rules that share a primary heuristic (e.g. <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87ade91ab1cd38237cb688634ed2b95a62e" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.SPT_SMPT</ref> and <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87a18355950aa0d135000b56aba39667cf3" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.SPT_SRWT</ref>) are collapsed to the same LINQ ordering since secondary metrics are not yet distinguished at the operation level.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>waitingOps</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The list of operations currently queued on the machine, in arrival order. Must not be modified during selection. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>allJobs</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The full job array, used to compute remaining-work metrics for <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87a9207d43f78389b34a02df21e4c33f724" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.SRT_SRWT</ref>, <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87a43f08a6810a17732c5bf5f20644ca7d6" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.SRT_SMPT</ref>, <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87a3ead285f50958d8aa6e59cf3fe61b421" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.LRT_MMUR</ref>, and <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87ae69ac1079473dee4c15dc7bb67c1cad3" kindref="member">DispatchingRule.MOR</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rule</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The dispatching rule that determines the selection priority.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1_1_operation" kindref="compound">Operation</ref> that should be started next, or <computeroutput>null</computeroutput> if <computeroutput>waitingOps</computeroutput> is null or empty. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
